questionRound.0.question.11.answer: I looked up to three cells ahead. When i foudn someone that had a row where both nubers were larger than the nubers in the other row  i based my decisions off of that color-person's.

I would check all of the squares and see which color(s) had a matrix that had the highest numbers in row X or row Y because that person would certainly pick the row that has the two highest numbers in it (in Display 3 that would be Purple). Then once I found that matrix  I would work backwards to see what the person before  them would pick because they would choose their answer base off of them (So Maroon would look at Purple and be able to choose with certainty). Then go backwards until it was my matrix. But it's all relative to whether or not the other people are using the same strategy
It is difficult to guess what the others will do without coordination  so I just tried to maximize my own payoff.
I saw which color had an absolute advantage of whatever letter they chose  and assumed that everyone else based their choices off of that as well.

As long as my tiles in one horizontal row were larger than the tiles on the other row i would choose that row without even worrying about what the guy to the right did  however if they were close in value i would look and see what the guy to right would do... i really didnt care that much about the others becasue i dont know for sure what they would do and it would ultimately come down to what i did.

I was using the numbers of the color whose answer affects my pay at first but then i realized some others were doing the same. I thought we were matched in an order of 6 people  so in order  whenever it was tose people's turn's i would think about what they would do since they were thinking like me and then chose the best possible answer for me.

I realized that most of the time the person who I was playing next to would choose the second highest number in their chart. I then looked at my chart in the same row as that person's second highest number  and chose the highest number of mine that was in that row. It worked almost every time.

For PURPLE  the payoff of choosing XP is always bigger from YP  so PURPLE will choose XP. Then MAROON will notice that and will choose whiever that has higher payoff corresponding to XP  which is YM. Then ORANGE will do the same thing and chooses YO  then BLUE chooses XB  then GREEN chooses YG  so as RED  I choose YR.

Look for the color where one row had higher values than the other row. That is the row that the player will pick. | Assume the player after knows this and is acting on his/her best interest and picks a choice that will lead to higher earnings.  | Assume the following player knows this as well and acts the same. | Trace through as many players as necessary to arrive at your own color and pick the option that leads to the better outcome.
No strategies  just the higher number

I randomly on a whim decided to go with a streak of X's initially. Then I watched out for situations where one choice of the player of the complimentary player was safer i.e. the two numbers in a row for one letter choice combine were higher than that for another row and picked my choice letter based on that. I did not care to analyze further on the choice beyond my complimentary color. The rest of the time  I picked randomly or kept to the X's.
maximize the token by choosing the dominent pay off
